---
// Static editorial content for City Traders Imperium
// Supports multiple sections via the `section` prop
interface Props {
  section: string;
  fallbackBody?: string;
}
const { section, fallbackBody } = Astro.props;
---

{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{/* CHALLENGES SECTION                                                  */}
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{section === "challenges" && (
<div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">

  <!-- Overview -->
  <p class="mb-4">
    City Traders Imperium offers four routes to funding: a One Step challenge, a Two Step challenge, and two Instant Funding models. All accounts operate in a simulated environment with no maximum time limits. Evaluation challenges (One Step, Two Step) use balance-based (static) drawdown, while Instant Funding accounts use trailing drawdown tied to the account balance.
  </p>

  <!-- Per-challenge summaries -->
  <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">One Step Challenge</p>
      <p>Single-phase evaluation with a 10% profit target. Account sizes from $2,500 to $100,000 with fees starting at $49.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-teal-600 font-semibold mt-1">80%–100% profit split · Balance-based drawdown · No time limit</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Two Step Challenge</p>
      <p>Two-phase evaluation: 10% target in Phase 1, 5% in Phase 2. Account sizes from $2,500 to $100,000 with fees starting at $39.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-teal-600 font-semibold mt-1">80%–100% profit split · Balance-based drawdown · No time limit</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Instant Funding</p>
      <p>Skip the evaluation entirely. Traders start with half the advertised balance and unlock the full amount after hitting the first 10% profit milestone. Account sizes from $2,500 to $80,000 with fees starting at $89.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-teal-600 font-semibold mt-1">Starts ~50% profit split (scales to 100%) · Trailing drawdown · Scaling to $2M per account</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Instant Funding Pro</p>
      <p>Higher-cost version starting at a higher funding level. Account sizes from $5,000 to $80,000 with fees starting at $329. Same 10% scaling milestones. Profit split starts around 50% and increases through milestones.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-teal-600 font-semibold mt-1">Starts ~50% profit split (scales to 100%) · Trailing drawdown · Accelerated path to larger capital</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── Comparison Table ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Challenge Comparison</h3>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-10">
    <table class="w-full text-sm whitespace-nowrap">
      <thead class="bg-slate-800 text-xs font-semibold text-white uppercase tracking-wide">
        <tr>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Attribute</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">One Step</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Two Step</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Instant Funding</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Instant Funding Pro</th>
